==English==

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb}}

# {{lb|en|American football}} Of a [[quarterback]] or other player in the [[backfield]], to take a number of steps back from the [[line of scrimmage]] immediately after the [[snap]] or [[hike]] of the ball, to avoid defenders.
#: ''The Tiger quarterback is '''dropping back''' to pass.''
# To move to a lower (or slower) position in a race or competition; to slow down so as to meet up with someone behind oneself

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|American football}} The act by a player in the [[backfield]] of [[drop back|dropping back]] from the [[line of scrimmage]] after the [[hike]] of the ball.
#: ''With his ankle injury his '''drop back''' is not pretty.''

